ExternalQAFrameworks.Label: National Skills Coalition: Quality Non-Degree Credential (NDC) Framework
Education Quality Outcomes Standards: Building Credential Currency Framework
Education Strategy Group: Quality Assurance Standards Framework

ExternalQAConstraints.Definition: There must be evidence of substantial job opportunities associated with the credential. Evidence must include quantitative data and direct communication with employers.

There must be transparent evidence of the competencies mastered by credential holders; competencies that align with expected job opportunities. A definition of a quality credential need not include any standard regarding length of time.
There must be evidence of the employment and earnings outcomes of individuals after obtaining the credential.

The credential would ideally stack to additional education or training. The gold standard is that credentials stack to additional education or training, but there is not a universal pathway to reach this standard so this is a preferred criterion for states.
Quality Non-Degree Credential (NDC) Framework Discussion Questions
Learning: Skills and competencies gained/ Licensing or professional certs or other cred + projects; self-identified; to be expanded
Completion: Number of students enrolled who finish program while meeting learning standards / Completing the program to self-defined competency level; could be connected to industry
Placement: Labor market position post-program / Getting new role; advancing in existing org; new or increased self-employment income
Earnings: Delta between pre- and post- program income / Self-reported income surveys before and after program matched to state labor data
Satisfaction: Program eval from students; IN expansion to employers / Post-program survey of students on several dimensions

Cross-sector collaboration: The SEA, higher education agency, and state workforce agency communicate and collaborate regularly to create a single cohesive state-level list of priority non-degree credentials. Resources and data are shared to drive work around common goals.

Labor market forcasting: The state identifies its priority in-demand, high-skill, high-wage occupations and credentials using rigorous thresholds for job demand, wage, and skill level. The list of priority occupations and credentials is uniform across state agencies.

Postsecondary credit for priority non-degree credentials: There is a statewide process for granting postsecondary credit in degree-granting programs to priority non-degree credentials. The state may also be considering how it may count priority non-degree credentials toward its postsecondary attainment goal.

Cost barrier removal for priority non-degree credential attainment: The state offers robust incentives to studentsincluding opportunities to cash in credentials for other valuable goods like college credit (through established articulation agreements for priority credentials) in addition to financial incentives such as waived exam fees and clearly communicates the value of these opportunities directly to students and families.
K-12 incentives: The state offers incentives to districts and schools that are differentiated in proportion to the value of the credential earned by the student.

Postsecondary and workforce incentives: The state incentivizes priority non-degree credential attainment with fundingeither indirectly through program tuition support or direct funding for credential exams. The state also includes priority non-degree credentials in its statewide postsecondary attainment goal.

K-12 incentivizing through accountability and reporting: Non-degree credential attainment is included in both statewide and federal accountability plans and is limited in scope to only priority credentials aligned to in-demand, high-skill, high-wage occupations.

Data collection: Data collected on credential attainment is:(a) student-level data, (b)complete (pass and faildata), and (c) validated either by data-sharing agreements with exam vendors or other means.
Data storage: The states data systems can record information on credential name, exam date, and exam result for each credential attempt a student makes.

PropertySets.Label: Credential Status Type
PropertySets.Definition: Type of official status of the credential; select from an enumeration of such types.

PropertySets.Label: CTID
PropertySets.Definition: Globally unique Credential Transparency Identifier (CTID) by which the creator, owner or provider of a resource recognizes it in transactions with the external environment (e.g., in verifiable claims involving the resource).

PropertySets.Label: Description
PropertySets.Definition: Statement, characterization or account of the entity.

PropertySets.Label: In Language
PropertySets.Definition: The primary language or languages of the entity, even if it makes use of other languages; e.g., a course offered in English to teach Spanish would have an inLanguage of English, while a credential in Quebec could have an inLanguage of both French and English.

PropertySets.Label: Name
PropertySets.Definition: Name or title of the resource.

PropertySets.Label: Subject Webpage
PropertySets.Definition: Webpage that describes this entity.

PropertySets.Label: Credential Type
PropertySets.Definition: The type of credential being described, including, but not limited to, certificate, certification, degree, and badge.
PropertySets.Comment: Credential Type is expressed as the class of credential (in JSON-LD, the @type), rather than via the ceterms:credentialType property/concept scheme.

PropertySets.Label: Owned or Offered By
PropertySets.Definition: The organization that owns and/or offers the credential.

PropertySets.Label: Advanced Standing From
PropertySets.Definition: Credential that has its time or cost reduced by another credential, assessment or learning opportunity.

PropertySets.Label: Audience Level Type
PropertySets.Definition: Type of level indicating a point in a progression through an educational or training context, for which the credential is intended; select from an existing enumeration of such types.

PropertySets.Label: Corequisite
PropertySets.Definition: Credentials that must be pursued concurrently.

PropertySets.Label: Date Effective
PropertySets.Definition: Effective date of the content of a credential, assessment or learning opportunity.

PropertySets.Label: Earnings
PropertySets.Definition: Entity describing aggregate credential holder earnings data.

PropertySets.Label: Employment Outcome
PropertySets.Definition: Entity describing aggregate data on jobs obtained with the credential by occupation and industry for a given period of time in a specific region.

PropertySets.Label: Estimated Cost
PropertySets.Definition: Estimated cost of a credential, learning opportunity or assessment.

PropertySets.Label: Estimated Duration
PropertySets.Definition: Estimated time it will take to complete a credential, learning opportunity or assessment.

PropertySets.Label: Financial Assistance
PropertySets.Definition: Entity that describes financial assistance for which this credential, assessment, or learning opportunity qualifies.

PropertySets.Label: Has Part
PropertySets.Definition: Indicates a separately identifiable and independently useful component of the entity.

PropertySets.Label: Holders
PropertySets.Definition: Entity describing the number and characteristics of credentialed individuals and their geographic location.

PropertySets.Label: Industry Type
PropertySets.Definition: Type of industry; select from an existing enumeration of such types such as the SIC, NAICS, and ISIC classifications.

PropertySets.Label: Is Advanced Standing For
PropertySets.Definition: This credential, assessment, or learning opportunity reduces the time or cost required to earn or complete the referenced credential, assessment, or learning opportunity.

PropertySets.Label: Is Part Of
PropertySets.Definition: Indicates another entity of which this entity is a component.

PropertySets.Label: Is Preparation For
PropertySets.Definition: This credential, assessment, or learning opportunity provides preparation for the credential, assessment, or learning opportunity being referenced.

PropertySets.Label: Is Recommended For
PropertySets.Definition: It is recommended to earn or complete this credential, assessment, or learning opportunity before attempting to earn or complete the referenced credential, assessment, or learning opportunity.

PropertySets.Label: Is Required For
PropertySets.Definition: This credential, assessment, or learning opportunity must be earned or completed prior to attempting to earn or complete the referenced credential, assessment, or learning opportunity.

PropertySets.Label: Jurisdiction
PropertySets.Definition: Geographic or political region in which the credential is formally applicable or an organization has authority to act.

PropertySets.Label: Keyword
PropertySets.Definition: Keyword or key phrase describing relevant aspects of an entity.

PropertySets.Label: Occupation Type
PropertySets.Definition: Type of occupation; select from an existing enumeration of such types.

PropertySets.Label: Preparation From
PropertySets.Definition: Another credential, learning opportunity or assessment that provides preparation for this credential, learning opportunity or assessment.

PropertySets.Label: Recommends
PropertySets.Definition: Recommended credential, learning opportunity or assessment.

PropertySets.Label: Requires
PropertySets.Definition: Requirement or set of requirements for this resource.

PropertySets.Label: Subject
PropertySets.Definition: Words or brief phrases describing the topicality of the entity; select subject terms from an existing enumeration of such terms.

PropertySets.Label: External Quality Assurance
PropertySets.Definition: Organizations can identify the external quality assurance (e.g., accreditation, approval, or recognition) that are issued to this Credential.

PropertySets.Label: Online or Physical Location
PropertySets.Definition: Link to and/or description of where the credential can be obtained.

PropertySets.Label: Accredited In
PropertySets.Definition: Region or political jurisdiction such as a state, province or locale in which the credential, learning opportunity or assessment is accredited.

PropertySets.Label: Administration Process
PropertySets.Definition: Entity describing the process by which a credential, assessment, organization, or aspects of it, are administered.

PropertySets.Label: Aggregate Data
PropertySets.Definition: Statistical information about the resource.

PropertySets.Label: Alternate Name
PropertySets.Definition: Alias for the entity including acronyms, alpha-numeric notations, and other forms of name abbreviations in common use such as PhD, MA, and BA.

PropertySets.Label: Appeal Process
PropertySets.Definition: Formal process for objecting to decisions of the organization regarding credentials, assessments or processes.

PropertySets.Label: Approved In
PropertySets.Definition: Region or political jurisdiction such as a state, province or locale in which an organization pronounces favorable judgment for this credential, assessment, learning opportunity, or organization.

PropertySets.Label: Assessment Delivery Type
PropertySets.Definition: Delivery type for the assessment for the credential.

PropertySets.Label: Audience Type
PropertySets.Definition: The type of audience for which the resource is applicable, intended, or useful; select from an existing enumeration of such types.

PropertySets.Label: Broad Alignment
PropertySets.Definition: Item that covers all of the relevant concepts in the item being described as well as additional relevant concepts.

PropertySets.Label: Common Conditions
PropertySets.Definition: Set constraints, prerequisites, entry conditions, or requirements that are shared across an organization, organizational subdivision, set of credentials, or category of entities and activities.

PropertySets.Label: Common Costs
PropertySets.Definition: Set of costs maintained at an organizational or sub-organizational level, which apply to this credential, assessment, or learning opportunity.

PropertySets.Label: Complaint Process
PropertySets.Definition: Process for handling complaints about a credential, or aspects of it including related learning opportunities and assessments.

PropertySets.Label: Copyright Holder
PropertySets.Definition: Person or organization holding the rights in copyright to entities such as credentials, learning opportunities, assessments, competencies or concept schemes.
